    put and patch differnce 
    Key Differences
Feature	PUT	PATCH
Update type	Full replace	Partial update
Data required	Complete object	Only changed fields
Risk	Data loss possible	Safe
Idempotent	Yes	Usually yes
Use case	Replace whole data	Update few fields

----"If we need a single API call that should pass whether the data exists or not, we use PUT. 
PUT supports idempotent behavior and can act as an upsert operation, meaning it updates if the resource exists and creates it if it does not."
